# Cursor Rules - Page Cloning Agent

When asked to clone a page, follow the instructions in PAGE_CLONING_AGENT.md

## Quick Command
```
Clone [URL] to [feature-name]
```

## Process (5 Phases)
1. **Navigate & Analyze** - Open URL, handle bot protection, scroll to load content
2. **Extract Data** - Get text, images, links, metadata; try API interception for dynamic sites
3. **Plan** - Determine route structure (static/dynamic), plan file organization
4. **Implement** - Create types, services, components, pages
5. **Verify & Iterate** - Check errors, compare with source, fix issues (max 5 iterations)

## Key Files
- `PAGE_CLONING_AGENT.md` - Complete instructions
- `src/lib/services/page-cloning-*.ts` - Analysis, extraction, planning, verification services
- `src/lib/utils/` - Sanitization, error handling, link processing utilities
- `src/lib/types/page-cloning.ts` - Type definitions

## Requirements
- Next.js Image for all images (add domains to next.config.js)
- Next.js Link for internal navigation
- External links: target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Responsive design (mobile-first)
- SEO metadata (title, description, OG tags)
- Loading skeleton + Error boundary
- TypeScript with proper types
- ISR caching (revalidate = 3600)

## Performance
- Virtualize lists with 100+ items
- Split large data files by category
- Use lazy loading for images
